lyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Loot rules discussion</span><hr size=1> Based on our discussion with Cyphonic during the Kael raid I would like to submit a suggested structure for loot on raids that will hopefully appeal to all. I hope we get lots of feedback on this and that we can all come up with a system that works.<br>
Rather than go into any reasons why this structure is necessary I will simply outline my proposed idea.<br>
-Alternate between random and the set structured loot rules.<br>
Example: currently their exists a rule that entitles only level 55+ characters the priviledge of rolling on Breast Plates. Alternating between raids that use this rule and a free raid where anyone involved in the raid can have a chance at rolling gives the characters lower than 55 something to &quot;shoot for&quot;.<br>
If an alternating system is going to be used it is important to not disclose whether the raid is Open or structured until it starts. This ensures that as many people as possible attend the raid...( otherwise those inelligible for item rolls will not come) <br>
-This idea can go even further and be done on individual item drops rather than the whole raid. Perhaps the next Breastplate that drops can be randomed to all involved in the raid...then the one after that follows the 55+ rule. This in itself could solve alot of problems and give everyone involved a fair chance. Those characters with a longer time put into the game still get their chances at loots, while younger characters have a chance at getting that really great piece of gear.<br>
-It is agreed that a loot list is too difficult to maintain..yet it is also agreed that some form of recording &quot;who has got what&quot; is necessary to prevent the same Luckier players from winning all the rolls. There are players who have attended all the raids and yet never won anything in a roll. I propose rather than maintain a list, people use goodwill and remember that they have won an item and let a fellow gamer who has not, roll in their place. Feedback on this point is very welcome..we must come up with something that works.<br>
-Point system. I have heard of some guilds that use a point system for determining who gets to roll on drops. A single point is awarded to the character for each raid they attend in the presence of guild officers. When a drop happns that several players want only those players that have &quot;#&quot; of points may roll. Once rolled there point total drops back to zero. This system is fair to all...as it rewards those who are involved in raids and lets the players rotate in and out of order.<br>
The negatives to this is who is to say How many points a certain player has...inflating of points will occur...and the casual player gets left in the dust in this system.<br>
In closing I invite all of you to add your input in an attempt to come up with a loot system that makes us all happier.<br>
What we need is constructive discussion and suggestions to loot arbitration. <br>
Naralli Ironsmith 52 warrior Order of the Black Sun<br>
