<br>
DISCLAIMER:  These are strictly examples, there are no implications towards anyone.<br>
<br>
It seems somewhat backwards for a just planable shaman (level 46) to recieve a chainmail tunic/leggings when we have 55+ rangers wearing treeweaves and ry'gorr.  That 46 shaman should attend the raid even though he/she might not get the tunic or leggings.  His/Her time will come around eventually.<br>
<br>
The same holds true for the plate classes.<br>
<br>
When it comes to passing on loot.  If you have the equilivant or better...DON'T ROLL.  If you're already wearing a kunark breastplate or greaves, DON'T ROLL.  If it's an item you're not going to use all the time, and someone else will, DON'T ROLL.  At our last Kael raid I saw several people pass on super nice loot...because they had better or because they thought someone else could better use it.  I commend these people.  They're looking at the big picture. <br>
<br>
The raid leaders, whomever they are at the time, have the authority to use discretion at any time regarding loot.  If/when this happens, the raid leaders will confer with each guilds leaders and officers in attendance.  That's how it's been in the past and that's probably how it will be in the future.<br>
<br>
We have another Kael raid on wednesday.  Let's not send our raid leaders, guild leaders, and guild officers tells unless they're happy tells.  Let's not bicker about loot, let's just go there and have a good time.   Despite the 289038403 tels from 390784986 people about 3459734965 things I had a pretty good time, let's do it again. <p>Neaadan<p>
